<br>
A bit of background.  levels 50 to 60 were introduced and IMHO balanced before the Pet PC and SOR nerfs.  They may explain why we are so screwed up now. Pets hit max less and miss so much more often than at all levels than when 50 to 60 were implemented in Kunark.<br>
<br>
VI abhores AFK EXP.<br>
<br>
Looking at those two.  <br>
<br>
here is my idea(s).<br>
<br>
Since VI does not want us to be able to get AFK exp and beta neutral pets seem to not be a full answer and I think VI would reason they take to much risk out of using a pet.  Just an observation not my idea.<br>
<br>
First and foremost remove the pet exp penalty !!!!!   No other class is so dependant on its pet, and rightfully so.  Now many necros do you see using their specre pet.  They solo without it.  No offence to necros, but a mage cannot solo without a pet anything.<br>
<br>
Keep the BO line buffing the same things as it does now, but increase its effectiveness by 10%<br>
<br>
Create a spell line that increases pet levels.  like the Burnout line there will be 1 to 5 versions.  The level increase will correspont to the number  Pet increase level II will increase pet 2 levels etc.<br>
<br>
Create a spell line that moves the pets from the PC tables to the NPC tables.  (Not sure if this one is possible, but sinces 50 to 60 magicians were created when pets were NPC's is shouldn't be overpowering.)  Make only say 3 of these spells.  1 affects pets up to level 30, cast at 12.  one affects pets 29 to 52, cast at 29, one affect 50+ pets, cast at 52.   or just one buff that affects them all.  Doesn't really matter to me.  The idea is to temporarily put pets back on the NPC &quot;to hit&quot; table.<br>
<br>
Now these will make out pets the total shredding machines they were before some of the nerfs, but here's the difference.  <br>
<br>
BO is 15 minutes.  <br>
Make the level increase 12.5 minutes. or 17.5<br>
Make the table change 10 minutes.  or 5 minutes or 20 minutes.<br>
<br>
The idea is that a pet cannot solo exp mobs without all of the buffs, and possibly a little help from the mage,  and being different durations, you would have to be there and not afk to keep the pet's buffs refreshed.  <br>
<br>
Will pets be able to solo 50+ mobs with all of these.  With the exeption of the 59+ and epic I doubt it.  <br>
<br>
What it will do is turn us back into the MASSIVE offensive force we were before and during the early days of Kunark.  Putting pets on neutral faction would be to much if these went in, as pet control would still be an issue.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway feel free to flame away, as I know you will.  <br>
<br>
